1
00:00:48,719 --> 00:00:50,763
Good morning, New York.
Scott Zoe here...

2
00:00:51,055 --> 00:00:55,100
...at 102. 7, WNEW-FM,
where rock lives.

3
00:00:55,309 --> 00:00:57,019
Beautiful autumn day
in the city...

4
00:00:57,311 --> 00:01:00,147
...and a great record coming
your way too.

5
00:01:29,009 --> 00:01:30,552
Ben!

6
00:01:33,055 --> 00:01:34,514
Ben!

7
00:01:36,933 --> 00:01:40,020
Get up, get up, get up!
Late, late, late!

8
00:01:40,270 --> 00:01:43,356
Come on, honey. Get up.
We're seriously late.

9
00:01:46,026 --> 00:01:49,029
You may think this is funny,
but this is so not...

10
00:01:49,237 --> 00:01:50,197
...funny.

11
00:01:51,239 --> 00:01:55,869
I'm not kidding anymore. You make
yourself appear right this instant.

12
00:02:01,750 --> 00:02:04,586
The clock is ticking, Ben!
Come on now!

13
00:02:09,758 --> 00:02:10,675
Anna?

14
00:02:10,925 --> 00:02:12,385
Oh good, you're already up.

15
00:02:12,635 --> 00:02:16,473
You forgot to wash my shirt.
Today is purple shirt day at school.

16
00:02:17,682 --> 00:02:19,225
I didn't forget.

17
00:02:19,767 --> 00:02:22,770
Actually, I was up half the night
thinking about it.

18
00:02:23,354 --> 00:02:24,731
Yeah, right.

19
00:02:25,273 --> 00:02:29,402
I concluded that you are too special
to look like everyone else.

20
00:02:29,652 --> 00:02:32,989
So, orangey-red. That's your colour.
Few can carry it off.

21
00:02:34,866 --> 00:02:36,826
-Help me find your brother.
-You lost Ben?

22
00:02:39,704 --> 00:02:41,748
I didn't lose Ben.

23
00:02:50,715 --> 00:02:52,341
All right, Ben, fine.

24
00:02:52,633 --> 00:02:54,760
You explain to your teacher
why you're late.

25
00:02:55,136 --> 00:02:59,182
Your daddy said he had an important
case and had to go to work early.

26
00:02:59,390 --> 00:03:02,643
And he left us here
to be responsible--

27
00:03:03,519 --> 00:03:04,437
Shit!

28
00:03:05,688 --> 00:03:06,939
You're so not funny.

29
00:03:07,189 --> 00:03:08,107
Not funny.

30
00:03:08,316 --> 00:03:11,569
You're also late, and that means
get dressed right now!

31
00:03:11,819 --> 00:03:14,905
Stay. No, stay. Ben! Ben!

32
00:03:15,156 --> 00:03:16,782
This is not funny!

33
00:03:17,199 --> 00:03:19,493
We've got to get you dressed.
We're running so late.

34
00:03:19,744 --> 00:03:21,620
This is not a game!

35
00:03:22,455 --> 00:03:24,248
Come on. Help me out.

36
00:03:25,791 --> 00:03:27,585
Come on! Really, we're so late.

37
00:03:27,793 --> 00:03:29,837
But I don't want
to go to school.

38
00:03:32,047 --> 00:03:32,882
Mommy!

39
00:03:33,174 --> 00:03:34,091
Mommy!

40
00:03:34,383 --> 00:03:35,926
Hi, sweetie!

41
00:03:37,469 --> 00:03:39,930
You look like you're
having such a good time.

42
00:03:40,222 --> 00:03:42,433
But we're running a little late.

43
00:03:42,641 --> 00:03:46,061
-You're supposed to wear purple.
-She forgot to wash it.

44
00:03:49,148 --> 00:03:50,774
What a hug!

45
00:03:53,861 --> 00:03:55,904
I'll handle it from here, lsabel.

46
00:03:57,656 --> 00:03:59,533
I'm sure you will, Jackie.

47
00:04:07,916 --> 00:04:10,169
Oh, my gosh!
She made you a lunch?

48
00:04:16,341 --> 00:04:17,801
Okay, come on.

49
00:04:32,024 --> 00:04:34,860
Mom, why are we listening
to this classical stuff?

50
00:04:35,110 --> 00:04:37,446
Because I like it,
and I'm driving.

51
00:04:37,696 --> 00:04:40,365
When you get a car,
you can pick the music.

52
00:04:41,158 --> 00:04:44,661
Why does lsabel wear Daddy's underpants?
Doesn't she have her own?

53
00:04:45,704 --> 00:04:49,291
I saw a whopping pile of laundry
sitting on the washing machine.

54
00:04:49,541 --> 00:04:53,128
-Perhaps her underpants are there.
-Right next to my purple shirt.

55
00:04:53,545 --> 00:04:55,005
I'm never speaking to her again.

56
00:04:55,255 --> 00:04:56,798
Never say never.
Here's your vitamins.

57
00:04:57,465 --> 00:04:59,342
She's always messing up my life.

58
00:04:59,593 --> 00:05:01,469
It's not fair to say ''always.''

59
00:05:01,761 --> 00:05:03,555
I hate her. She's such a witch.

60
00:05:03,847 --> 00:05:05,557
No name-calling.
Use your words.

61
00:05:06,141 --> 00:05:07,309
I hate when you say that.

62
00:05:07,559 --> 00:05:10,729
That's a beginning.
'' Hate'' is an acceptable word.

63
00:05:10,979 --> 00:05:14,899
Just be careful to use it
only when you truly detest something.

64
00:05:15,275 --> 00:05:16,192
Like what?

65
00:05:16,443 --> 00:05:17,986
Well, like...

66
00:05:18,236 --> 00:05:21,156
...Uranus. I hate that.
It's a terrible name for a planet.

67
00:05:21,948 --> 00:05:23,575
Uranus!

68
00:05:24,742 --> 00:05:26,286
And the hokey-pokey.

69
00:05:26,619 --> 00:05:30,415
I hate it. Putting your foot in
and out at weddings. It's terrible.

70
00:05:33,918 --> 00:05:36,838
I hate when you do that!
I can smell your breakfast.

71
00:05:37,046 --> 00:05:38,923
Point well-taken.

72
00:05:42,927 --> 00:05:46,597
Ladies, let's just calm down.
She'll be here.

73
00:05:46,848 --> 00:05:48,975
Isabel, where are you?
Come on. Any word?

74
00:05:49,267 --> 00:05:50,268
She's on her way.

75
00:05:50,518 --> 00:05:52,645
-She's on her way. I promise.
-Oh, really?

76
00:05:52,854 --> 00:05:54,021
How do you know?

77
00:05:54,272 --> 00:05:56,065
I'm here! I'm sorry I'm late.

78
00:05:56,357 --> 00:05:57,525
What a crisis!

79
00:05:57,775 --> 00:06:00,611
White pants, black top?
And the white or black bra?

80
00:06:00,820 --> 00:06:02,363
And then I picked this....

81
00:06:02,655 --> 00:06:04,782
-All righty.
-I'm here. I'm lame.

82
00:06:04,991 --> 00:06:06,951
You got a Froot Loop
in your hair.

83
00:06:16,377 --> 00:06:20,923
Get me a digital camera right now.
Russell, get this out of here, please.

84
00:06:21,507 --> 00:06:22,675
Come on, boys!

85
00:06:28,889 --> 00:06:30,433
Why is she shooting this?

86
00:06:31,058 --> 00:06:33,185
Isabel, we have been
waiting for an hour.

87
00:06:33,394 --> 00:06:36,480
I know. I'm sorry.
It won't happen again.

88
00:06:36,730 --> 00:06:38,524
Why are you shooting this?

89
00:06:39,108 --> 00:06:40,818
Because I'm brilliant.

90
00:06:41,068 --> 00:06:42,862
And I see something you don't.

91
00:06:43,112 --> 00:06:45,239
So stand back and trust me,
why don't you?

92
00:06:45,489 --> 00:06:48,742
I trust you. But why are you
shooting the craft service guy...

93
00:06:48,993 --> 00:06:53,205
...when I've got 5 male models
in expensive suits over here?

94
00:06:53,497 --> 00:06:57,001
Thank you, ladies. Lovely.
That's a wrap, everybody!

95
00:06:58,043 --> 00:06:59,420
No, it's not a wrap!

96
00:07:00,796 --> 00:07:03,465
She's kidding.
You were kidding, aren't you?

97
00:07:03,757 --> 00:07:07,261
I'm not kidding. And if you
meet me here in an hour...

98
00:07:07,511 --> 00:07:09,638
...l will prove to you
why you hired me...

99
00:07:09,888 --> 00:07:12,391
...even though I wouldn't
sleep with you.

100
00:07:18,105 --> 00:07:20,399
She's got such a
great sense of humor.

101
00:07:25,696 --> 00:07:26,780
Wait.

102
00:07:29,866 --> 00:07:31,243
Let's see...

103
00:07:31,660 --> 00:07:32,828
...if I can save...

104
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,913
...both our jobs.

105
00:07:39,418 --> 00:07:41,378
-Interesting.
-Look at that.

106
00:07:42,921 --> 00:07:45,674
Wow! It's the
little guy in the suit.

107
00:07:46,216 --> 00:07:47,592
-What do you think?
-I like it.

108
00:07:47,843 --> 00:07:48,969
I like it. Good work.

109
00:07:49,219 --> 00:07:51,096
I like it too. Very creative.

110
00:07:51,346 --> 00:07:52,639
Thank you.

111
00:07:52,931 --> 00:07:54,891
Congratulations, Duncan.

112
00:07:58,979 --> 00:08:00,522
That suit takes
pounds off of him.

113
00:08:00,814 --> 00:08:03,108
While change is exhilarating
for an adult...

114
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:05,986
...it can be quite a challenge
for a child.

115
00:08:08,780 --> 00:08:09,948
I won't get that.

116
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:13,076
It's fine.

117
00:08:13,451 --> 00:08:14,494
Change.

118
00:08:14,786 --> 00:08:16,079
You were talking about change.

119
00:08:16,371 --> 00:08:19,874
The fact that you two are remarrying
obviously has Anna overjoyed.

120
00:08:20,125 --> 00:08:22,585
And she's excited about
the move to Switzerland.

121
00:08:23,086 --> 00:08:25,630
She said we are remarrying?

122
00:08:26,172 --> 00:08:29,676
My concern is that Anna seems
apathetic towards her work...

123
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:32,137
...knowing she's leaving
before this semester.

124
00:08:32,428 --> 00:08:35,014
-Mrs. Franklin, we are not--
-No plans on getting....

125
00:08:35,265 --> 00:08:38,518
-Remarried. There's no move--
-To Switzerland.

126
00:08:39,769 --> 00:08:40,770
Really?

127
00:08:41,020 --> 00:08:41,938
Really.

128
00:08:42,855 --> 00:08:47,068
Well, then, my concern
for Anna is that she--

129
00:08:48,403 --> 00:08:49,862
-Are you here?
-I'm here.

130
00:08:50,071 --> 00:08:52,365
-You don't seem like you're here.
-I'm here.

131
00:08:52,573 --> 00:08:56,077
The judge is ruling on a motion
that could make or break my case.

132
00:08:56,327 --> 00:08:59,414
-But have I answered my beeper?
-So turn it off.

133
00:09:00,706 --> 00:09:03,626
I'm wondering if anything
at home could be...

134
00:09:03,876 --> 00:09:07,380
...intensifying Anna's need
to create this fantasy.

135
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:09,924
I've been seeing another woman.

136
00:09:10,174 --> 00:09:12,426
He's seen a number of women.

137
00:09:12,677 --> 00:09:16,180
But I've been seeing one woman
for the past year.

138
00:09:16,430 --> 00:09:20,476
After discussing it with her
and the kids, she moved in last month.

139
00:09:20,768 --> 00:09:21,936
She's half his age.

140
00:09:22,186 --> 00:09:25,356
-Isabel's not half my age.
-We're not discussing your age.

141
00:09:25,606 --> 00:09:28,859
When the children visit,
they want to be with their father.

142
00:09:29,068 --> 00:09:32,238
They want to be a part of my life.
Isabel's part of my life.

143
00:09:32,780 --> 00:09:36,909
Mr. Harrison, I hear you talking
about your life, your needs.

144
00:09:37,159 --> 00:09:39,662
But are you in touch
with what Anna needs?

145
00:09:40,371 --> 00:09:44,291
Anna needs a safe and loving home.
What I'm trying to give her.

146
00:09:44,583 --> 00:09:48,170
-That's what she already had.
-I'd walk through fire for Anna.

147
00:09:48,462 --> 00:09:50,756
Gladly. Any day of the week.

148
00:09:51,006 --> 00:09:53,217
Except Thursday, when lsabel
forgot to pick them up.

149
00:09:53,425 --> 00:09:55,928
Jackie, she was 5 minutes late,
for chrissakes!

150
00:09:56,553 --> 00:09:58,180
She was 5 minutes late!

151
00:09:58,472 --> 00:10:02,393
I wonder if Anna could be
responding to the hostility...

152
00:10:02,643 --> 00:10:05,646
...between your girlfriend
and Mrs. Harrison.

153
00:10:05,896 --> 00:10:08,732
Well, of course she's
responding to it.

154
00:10:09,274 --> 00:10:13,404
Do you think this is easy for us?
Do you think it's easy for Jackie...

155
00:10:13,695 --> 00:10:16,365
...to see her kids looked after
by another woman?

156
00:10:16,615 --> 00:10:20,911
Not to mention, a woman who really has
no experience being a mother.

157
00:10:21,495 --> 00:10:24,248
Of course Jackie's
going to be irrational...

158
00:10:24,456 --> 00:10:25,541
...hostile...

159
00:10:25,791 --> 00:10:27,167
...defensive.

160
00:10:28,835 --> 00:10:30,087
Thank you, Luke.

161
00:10:35,509 --> 00:10:36,969
Why would I say...

162
00:10:37,177 --> 00:10:38,804
...you're getting back together?

163
00:10:39,096 --> 00:10:42,766
People make up stories about
things they wish would happen.

164
00:10:43,016 --> 00:10:45,143
Why would I want that to happen?

165
00:10:45,394 --> 00:10:48,230
Okay, pick a card. Any card.

166
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:49,648
Because you're upset.

167
00:10:49,981 --> 00:10:51,858
Because lsabel moved in and--

168
00:10:52,109 --> 00:10:55,362
I'm not upset. I won't
get myself upset over her.

169
00:10:55,821 --> 00:10:57,030
Tear it in half.

170
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:58,657
Look, sweetie.

171
00:10:58,865 --> 00:11:00,075
-If it means--
-Again.

172
00:11:01,326 --> 00:11:02,160
Again.

173
00:11:03,203 --> 00:11:04,162
If you want--

174
00:11:04,412 --> 00:11:05,497
And again.

175
00:11:06,164 --> 00:11:07,249
Time out.

176
00:11:08,124 --> 00:11:12,504
If you don't want to talk
about this now, you don't have to.

177
00:11:13,255 --> 00:11:15,131
But don't look at me and lie.

178
00:11:15,674 --> 00:11:17,634
It hurts my feelings,
I get angry....

179
00:11:18,510 --> 00:11:21,680
You're only allowed so many lies
before it shows in your face...

180
00:11:21,888 --> 00:11:23,682
...and you wind up looking like....

181
00:11:25,058 --> 00:11:25,892
Like who?

182
00:11:26,142 --> 00:11:29,312
He's not President anymore,
so why be petty?

183
00:11:31,815 --> 00:11:33,858
I'm sorry I said it.

184
00:11:34,734 --> 00:11:36,528
I guess sometimes I just....

185
00:11:37,695 --> 00:11:40,865
Sometimes I do wish
you and Daddy would....

186
00:11:41,241 --> 00:11:42,367
Well, you know.

187
00:11:44,994 --> 00:11:48,706
I figured if I said it out loud,
it just might come true.

188
00:11:49,540 --> 00:11:50,708
Yeah, I know.

189
00:12:08,559 --> 00:12:12,396
It's not that I can't cook.
It's that I choose not to cook.

190
00:12:12,647 --> 00:12:15,316
-There's a big difference.
-You don't have to cook.

191
00:12:15,650 --> 00:12:17,860
Could we save some
of the wine?

192
00:12:19,946 --> 00:12:22,615
-I need it for the sauce.
-Too late.

193
00:12:23,616 --> 00:12:24,867
Hi, honey.

194
00:12:36,462 --> 00:12:37,838
You better get it.

195
00:12:44,595 --> 00:12:47,431
-Who's there?
-Nobody there.

196
00:12:52,353 --> 00:12:53,521
I missed you today.

197
00:12:53,812 --> 00:12:56,190
I missed you too.
I miss you every day.

198
00:12:56,398 --> 00:12:57,525
How was your day, baby?

199
00:12:57,775 --> 00:13:00,527
It was pretty good, except
I got to go back to Pittsburgh.

200
00:13:00,736 --> 00:13:03,405
Yeah, I got to go
tomorrow till Sunday.

201
00:13:04,698 --> 00:13:06,325
But I'll have to order in.

202
00:13:06,659 --> 00:13:09,745
Well, we got the kids
for the weekend, so I figured...

203
00:13:09,953 --> 00:13:11,997
...that you and the kids...

204
00:13:12,206 --> 00:13:14,792
...and me could all go...

205
00:13:15,292 --> 00:13:17,336
...to Pittsburgh together.

206
00:13:17,878 --> 00:13:19,254
Never going to happen.

207
00:13:19,463 --> 00:13:23,133
No? Come on! We could get
a great hotel room.

208
00:13:23,342 --> 00:13:25,636
We could take in
a baseball game or something.

209
00:13:25,886 --> 00:13:28,138
-What do you think?
-Pass.

210
00:13:28,680 --> 00:13:31,850
All right. Then I'll
call the babysitter.

211
00:13:32,142 --> 00:13:33,352
What for?

212
00:13:33,644 --> 00:13:36,480
Well, I don't expect you
to handle them yourself.

213
00:13:40,776 --> 00:13:41,735
What?

214
00:13:42,653 --> 00:13:46,323
Can't handle them myself.
That's what you mean, isn't it?

215
00:13:47,532 --> 00:13:48,492
No.

216
00:14:06,343 --> 00:14:09,095
You don't trust me to be
alone with your kids.

217
00:14:09,387 --> 00:14:10,388
Yes, I do.

218
00:14:10,680 --> 00:14:12,474
Of course I do.
It's just that--

219
00:14:12,682 --> 00:14:14,643
-What?
-They're a handful.

220
00:14:15,435 --> 00:14:18,688
Luke, keeping me apart from them
is like saying...

221
00:14:18,980 --> 00:14:21,191
...'' Kids, this is fun.
Keep on hating her.''

222
00:14:21,441 --> 00:14:24,110
-They don't hate you.
-Really?

223
00:14:24,861 --> 00:14:27,447
Look in their eyes.
Look in your ex-wife's eyes.

224
00:14:28,281 --> 00:14:31,368
Jackie's just protecting her kids.
What do you expect?

225
00:14:31,910 --> 00:14:35,747
It's complicated. You don't
understand. You don't have kids.

226
00:14:37,749 --> 00:14:42,045
So it's just complicated
for you and Jackie.

227
00:14:42,295 --> 00:14:46,841
For me, it's pretty simple
because I don't have kids.

228
00:14:47,091 --> 00:14:51,721
I'm just trying to give you guys
time to get used to living together.

229
00:14:51,930 --> 00:14:52,847
All right then.

230
00:14:53,348 --> 00:14:57,226
Back off just a little bit
and give me a chance, okay?

231
00:15:10,239 --> 00:15:11,949
What is your problem, asshole?

232
00:15:12,325 --> 00:15:14,118
You are my problem!

233
00:15:19,373 --> 00:15:21,584
You're absolutely right, baby.

234
00:15:22,251 --> 00:15:26,631
Your kids don't hate me.
I'm just paranoid. Call your daughter.

235
00:15:31,719 --> 00:15:33,179
I trust you.

236
00:15:34,055 --> 00:15:35,014
Really?

237
00:15:35,264 --> 00:15:37,391
I'll give you a chance
if you still want it.

238
00:15:39,644 --> 00:15:40,936
-I do.
-Are you sure?

239
00:15:41,187 --> 00:15:42,104
Yes.

240
00:15:43,314 --> 00:15:44,357
Okay.

241
00:15:48,152 --> 00:15:50,196
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

242
00:15:51,197 --> 00:15:53,324
Don't fight with me
when I'm hungry.

243
00:15:56,327 --> 00:15:58,370
How long will you be out of town?

244
00:15:58,621 --> 00:15:59,914
Till Sunday morning.

245
00:16:00,164 --> 00:16:01,624
I'm worried.

246
00:16:01,832 --> 00:16:02,791
About what?

247
00:16:03,042 --> 00:16:05,711
About being alone
with her all weekend.

248
00:16:06,003 --> 00:16:07,463
What if she burns the place down?

249
00:16:07,713 --> 00:16:09,757
Just keep an eye on her...

250
00:16:09,965 --> 00:16:12,968
...and make sure the
