589
00:39:47,787 --> 00:39:48,997
Is that a weekday?

590
00:39:51,332 --> 00:39:53,376
I think it's a Thursday.

591
00:39:53,835 --> 00:39:57,588
You want to take a 1 2-year-old
to a concert on a school night?

592
00:40:00,675 --> 00:40:04,303
I thought it would be something nice
we could do together.

593
00:40:05,096 --> 00:40:06,305
It's ridiculous.

594
00:40:06,639 --> 00:40:07,932
She's too young.

595
00:40:44,093 --> 00:40:45,469
It spread?

596
00:40:45,970 --> 00:40:46,929
But I did--

597
00:40:47,555 --> 00:40:51,183
I did everything right.
Everything I was supposed to do.

598
00:40:51,392 --> 00:40:55,312
We found some cells in your
lymph nodes. In three of them.

599
00:40:57,856 --> 00:41:00,609
But you said last time
that you got it all.

600
00:41:00,859 --> 00:41:03,445
If you were wrong last time,
you could be wrong--

601
00:41:03,737 --> 00:41:07,157
The last time was a year ago.

602
00:41:07,449 --> 00:41:11,036
We found a tiny lump, we treated it.
We thought we got it all.

603
00:41:11,245 --> 00:41:13,997
We were hopeful, but there
were no guarantees.

604
00:41:16,583 --> 00:41:17,793
But people--

605
00:41:18,919 --> 00:41:22,631
We can beat it. I mean,
people beat it all the time, right?

606
00:41:22,881 --> 00:41:25,551
-Every day, more and more.
-So what's the plan?

607
00:41:25,843 --> 00:41:28,345
What do we do?
Another round of radiation?

608
00:41:29,930 --> 00:41:31,390
Chemotherapy.

609
00:41:33,684 --> 00:41:35,143
That's necessary?

610
00:41:37,312 --> 00:41:39,106
Let's give it our best shot.

611
00:41:41,608 --> 00:41:42,984
Right. Okay.

612
00:41:44,111 --> 00:41:45,904
I got to get the kids.

613
00:41:46,154 --> 00:41:48,281
We'll discuss this at
your next appointment.

614
00:41:48,532 --> 00:41:51,618
You should share this with
your kids and ex-husband.

615
00:41:51,868 --> 00:41:54,621
How would their worrying
make any difference?

616
00:41:54,871 --> 00:41:56,498
Sooner than later...

617
00:41:57,749 --> 00:41:59,000
...you need to.

618
00:42:02,295 --> 00:42:03,588
Think about it.

619
00:42:21,523 --> 00:42:22,607
I see her.

620
00:42:31,032 --> 00:42:33,493
-Thanks for coming.
-You're welcome.

621
00:42:33,952 --> 00:42:35,119
You look pretty.

622
00:42:35,411 --> 00:42:36,579
Thanks.

623
00:42:39,040 --> 00:42:39,874
Listen--

624
00:42:40,124 --> 00:42:43,294
I'm glad you called.
I want to tell you something too.

625
00:42:44,504 --> 00:42:45,588
You go first.

626
00:42:45,838 --> 00:42:47,632
Let me have a drink here.

627
00:42:56,432 --> 00:42:59,352
I'm going to ask lsabel
to marry me.

628
00:43:06,651 --> 00:43:08,945
I know you don't
think much of her.

629
00:43:10,029 --> 00:43:11,989
She's a special person.

630
00:43:12,323 --> 00:43:14,367
She really is, Jackie.

631
00:43:17,078 --> 00:43:18,621
Why are you telling me?

632
00:43:19,330 --> 00:43:20,957
I want your okay.

633
00:43:21,165 --> 00:43:23,209
-You don't need my approval.
-The kids do.

634
00:43:23,501 --> 00:43:26,837
Good evening. Would you and
your wife care to look at the menu?

635
00:43:27,088 --> 00:43:28,714
I'm not his wife.

636
00:43:28,965 --> 00:43:30,508
No, thank you.

637
00:43:31,467 --> 00:43:34,720
Give me a drink though, please.
Whatever this is.

638
00:43:36,430 --> 00:43:40,017
I think it's going to be
hard for the kids.

639
00:43:40,643 --> 00:43:43,813
I was hoping we could
tell them together.

640
00:43:44,021 --> 00:43:46,774
And that'd make it easier for the kids?
Or for you?

641
00:43:47,066 --> 00:43:51,445
You can't just decide to be a
''we'' and '' us'' whenever it's convenient.

642
00:43:51,695 --> 00:43:53,739
-We are--
-We're over. We are over.

643
00:43:53,989 --> 00:43:56,909
We are still their parents
for the next 1 00 years.

644
00:44:13,550 --> 00:44:14,760
Why?

645
00:44:17,346 --> 00:44:20,182
Just tell me why you
think this marriage...

646
00:44:21,433 --> 00:44:23,811
...is going to work
and ours didn't.

647
00:44:43,872 --> 00:44:47,209
-What did you want to talk to me about?
-Nothing. It's--

648
00:44:49,419 --> 00:44:50,670
I think we have...

649
00:44:51,671 --> 00:44:55,092
...quite enough to deal with
just with your news.

650
00:45:15,153 --> 00:45:16,279
Good morning.

651
00:45:16,529 --> 00:45:18,073
Good morning, baby.

652
00:45:19,991 --> 00:45:21,785
I've got something for you.

653
00:45:22,077 --> 00:45:23,244
You do?

654
00:45:27,040 --> 00:45:29,709
But you have to wake up
to get it.

655
00:45:45,141 --> 00:45:46,684
I'm awake.

656
00:46:11,501 --> 00:46:12,710
You shouldn't have?

657
00:46:15,004 --> 00:46:17,215
The first time I got married...

658
00:46:17,924 --> 00:46:20,384
...we'd been together since college.

659
00:46:21,052 --> 00:46:22,929
Marriage...

660
00:46:23,179 --> 00:46:25,556
...just seemed like the next step.

661
00:46:26,724 --> 00:46:29,310
It was just something
that happened.

662
00:46:30,561 --> 00:46:33,898
But I think for two people
to really love each other...

663
00:46:34,732 --> 00:46:38,152
...to really commit to each other...

664
00:46:38,903 --> 00:46:40,196
...it has to be...

665
00:46:42,573 --> 00:46:44,533
...an act of will.

666
00:46:45,743 --> 00:46:47,369
Or a decision.

667
00:46:48,079 --> 00:46:52,374
And I think two people have to
live that decision every day.

668
00:46:53,793 --> 00:46:57,463
Even when things are hard
and you feel like giving up...

669
00:46:57,796 --> 00:46:59,256
...you have to...

670
00:47:00,132 --> 00:47:02,635
...hang on to that decision...

671
00:47:05,971 --> 00:47:07,681
...that choice...

672
00:47:07,932 --> 00:47:09,808
...to love each other.

673
00:47:10,434 --> 00:47:12,811
Even if it's only by a thread.

674
00:47:17,483 --> 00:47:19,985
I let that thread break once.

675
00:47:21,653 --> 00:47:23,363
This time, it won't.

676
00:47:33,373 --> 00:47:34,666
Will you marry me?

677
00:47:35,501 --> 00:47:36,418
Yes.

678
00:47:37,044 --> 00:47:38,086
Yes, I will.

679
00:47:49,389 --> 00:47:53,310
-Sweetheart, don't get upset.
-I'm not upset. Why would I be upset?

680
00:47:53,977 --> 00:47:56,730
No one asked me
when you got a divorce.

681
00:47:56,980 --> 00:47:58,940
No one asked if
I wanted a new mother.

682
00:47:59,149 --> 00:48:01,610
No one even asked me
if I liked her.

683
00:48:01,860 --> 00:48:05,614
If you don't care about keeping our
family together, why should l?

684
00:48:05,822 --> 00:48:08,742
Daddy and I tried very hard.
Really, we did.

685
00:48:08,950 --> 00:48:11,786
No, you didn't! All you did
was name-call. I heard you.

686
00:48:11,995 --> 00:48:15,248
You didn't even try to
use real words.

687
00:48:17,292 --> 00:48:21,588
Baby, lsabel's not going
to take my place as your mom.

688
00:48:22,756 --> 00:48:26,551
It's just that lsabel's
going to be in your life...

689
00:48:27,302 --> 00:48:29,804
...and hopefully, you can
learn to accept her.

690
00:48:35,560 --> 00:48:36,728
Sweetheart.

691
00:48:38,521 --> 00:48:39,647
Honey.

692
00:48:42,442 --> 00:48:45,111
You know, life is
full of hard things.

693
00:48:45,361 --> 00:48:47,572
Sometimes it isn't fair.

694
00:48:48,823 --> 00:48:50,200
But you have a choice.

695
00:48:50,408 --> 00:48:54,621
You can either take the hard things
and make your life better...

696
00:48:54,871 --> 00:48:56,748
...or you can make it worse.

697
00:48:57,332 --> 00:48:58,416
Like how?

698
00:49:02,587 --> 00:49:03,504
Like...

699
00:49:04,172 --> 00:49:07,425
...trying to see
the good side of lsabel...

700
00:49:08,676 --> 00:49:11,012
...and what she brings
to your father's life.

701
00:49:11,637 --> 00:49:12,805
And to yours.

702
00:49:15,058 --> 00:49:17,018
There comes a time
in every family...

703
00:49:17,310 --> 00:49:19,520
...when you've got to be there
for each other.

704
00:49:23,065 --> 00:49:24,609
I'll be there for you.

705
00:49:26,986 --> 00:49:28,696
How about you, buddy?

706
00:49:29,947 --> 00:49:30,948
Yeah.

707
00:49:31,699 --> 00:49:32,992
You'll be there?

708
00:49:46,797 --> 00:49:47,882
Damn it!

709
00:49:57,725 --> 00:49:58,809
What's the problem?

710
00:50:00,769 --> 00:50:01,896
Nothing.

711
00:50:11,155 --> 00:50:12,865
It looks good.

712
00:50:13,115 --> 00:50:15,409
I can't get the trees
to look real.

713
00:50:18,454 --> 00:50:19,913
Mind if I try?

714
00:50:21,832 --> 00:50:24,084
I already messed it up anyway.

715
00:50:27,129 --> 00:50:28,088
Let's see.

716
00:50:28,589 --> 00:50:31,008
First a little brush smooshing.

717
00:50:31,717 --> 00:50:32,926
''Smooshing.''

718
00:50:33,177 --> 00:50:34,887
Very technical term.

719
00:50:50,444 --> 00:50:52,654
Cool! Where'd you learn
how to do that?

720
00:50:52,863 --> 00:50:55,782
I took an art class
when I was at NYU.

721
00:50:59,328 --> 00:51:01,288
Why don't you give it a try?

722
00:51:03,707 --> 00:51:06,251
It helps if you make
that little....

723
00:51:17,470 --> 00:51:18,555
Thanks.

724
00:51:20,307 --> 00:51:21,391
You're welcome.

725
00:51:31,860 --> 00:51:34,446
I was thinking about
what you said about lsabel.

726
00:51:34,696 --> 00:51:36,823
You know, seeing
the good side of her.

727
00:51:37,032 --> 00:51:38,825
And you're right.

728
00:51:39,075 --> 00:51:41,036
She knows all about
clothes and stuff.

729
00:51:41,244 --> 00:51:44,664
And she knows every
rock and roll song ever written.

730
00:51:45,248 --> 00:51:47,125
She's like a kid herself.

731
00:51:47,417 --> 00:51:49,043
Like a big sister.

732
00:51:50,003 --> 00:51:52,505
She knows the cool
junk food places.

733
00:51:52,755 --> 00:51:53,673
I'll bet.

734
00:51:54,549 --> 00:51:57,135
Once you get to know her,
she's kind of cool.

735
00:51:59,929 --> 00:52:02,473
But don't tell her I told you.

736
00:52:04,726 --> 00:52:05,685
It's our secret.

737
00:52:07,020 --> 00:52:08,396
Thanks.

738
00:52:09,522 --> 00:52:11,399
Ben, wait up!

739
00:53:14,128 --> 00:53:16,589
Did you have a good day?

740
00:53:16,839 --> 00:53:18,549
You're lucky because...

741
00:53:19,133 --> 00:53:22,386
...you get to watch a tape.
I'm going out. Colleen's baby-sitting.

742
00:53:22,636 --> 00:53:23,887
Yeah! Cool!

743
00:53:24,388 --> 00:53:25,222
And you...

744
00:53:25,431 --> 00:53:27,141
...are wearing makeup.

745
00:53:28,142 --> 00:53:30,269
Well, no.
Isabel gave it to me.

746
00:53:31,979 --> 00:53:34,273
She put it on in the car,
playing around.

747
00:53:35,858 --> 00:53:40,237
You don't see that color in the
afternoon, except on working girls.

748
00:53:40,863 --> 00:53:43,949
Anyway, wash your face, because...

749
00:53:44,616 --> 00:53:46,410
...you and I are going out.

750
00:53:46,618 --> 00:53:48,495
On a school night?

751
00:53:50,038 --> 00:53:51,206
Pearl Jam?!

752
00:53:52,457 --> 00:53:56,211
-Mom, you are the coolest!
-You only live once, right?

753
00:53:57,129 --> 00:53:59,172
Isn't my mom the coolest?

754
00:54:02,634 --> 00:54:04,428
It was a great idea. Thanks.

755
00:54:06,513 --> 00:54:07,681
Have fun.

756
00:54:19,401 --> 00:54:22,404
Chemotherapy. There's
a day's dose stored here.

757
00:54:22,612 --> 00:54:25,365
This is a portable IV. Feel it.

758
00:54:26,658 --> 00:54:27,742
It's pretty light.

759
00:54:27,951 --> 00:54:31,788
Nice and slim. You can wear it
