00:54:32,163 --> 00:54:34,833
-You can hide it under your clothes.
-That's cool.

761
00:54:36,668 --> 00:54:38,211
Side effects?

762
00:54:39,129 --> 00:54:42,215
Some days you'll experience
drowsiness, nausea...

763
00:54:42,424 --> 00:54:44,884
...and other days you'll
feel perfectly fine.

764
00:54:45,927 --> 00:54:47,637
Am I going to lose my hair?

765
00:54:48,138 --> 00:54:48,972
Maybe.

766
00:54:49,264 --> 00:54:52,350
Maybe not. It varies
with each person.

767
00:54:53,393 --> 00:54:54,644
Let's do it.

768
00:54:55,645 --> 00:54:56,688
Good.

769
00:54:57,438 --> 00:54:58,356
When?

770
00:54:59,607 --> 00:55:01,901
I'm available tomorrow evening.

771
00:55:02,151 --> 00:55:04,904
Tomorrow's bad.
Spaghetti and meatball night.

772
00:55:05,154 --> 00:55:06,948
Ben really looks forward--

773
00:55:07,198 --> 00:55:09,409
Okay, tomorrow's good. Fine.

774
00:55:19,877 --> 00:55:21,587
Hi, honey. How you doing?

775
00:55:22,004 --> 00:55:24,465
Mom, I've been
waiting for your call.

776
00:55:24,966 --> 00:55:27,301
-You won't believe it.
-What?

777
00:55:27,552 --> 00:55:30,388
-I'm telepathetic.
-You mean telepathic.

778
00:55:30,638 --> 00:55:32,265
That's what I said.

779
00:55:32,515 --> 00:55:36,102
I just discovered it today.
I can read minds.

780
00:55:36,310 --> 00:55:37,395
No way.

781
00:55:37,645 --> 00:55:40,898
I just tried it with Dad
and lsabel, and guess what.

782
00:55:41,148 --> 00:55:42,149
What?

783
00:55:42,483 --> 00:55:45,152
I always knew exactly
what they were thinking.

784
00:55:45,778 --> 00:55:47,405
That is incredible.

785
00:55:47,655 --> 00:55:49,615
-Want me to read yours?
-Absolutely.

786
00:55:49,865 --> 00:55:53,035
-Think real hard about something.
-I'm thinking.

787
00:55:53,285 --> 00:55:55,246
Close your eyes.

788
00:55:56,288 --> 00:55:58,332
Concentrate.

789
00:55:58,749 --> 00:56:00,459
I am concentrating.

790
00:56:03,712 --> 00:56:05,840
You're thinking about me!

791
00:56:07,883 --> 00:56:09,426
That is amazing.

792
00:56:10,052 --> 00:56:11,011
What else?

793
00:56:11,804 --> 00:56:15,057
You're wishing you were
here instead of where you are.

794
00:56:16,350 --> 00:56:18,310
That's for sure.

795
00:56:18,519 --> 00:56:20,229
Where are you, anyway?

796
00:56:20,896 --> 00:56:23,566
I'm in bed, with the flu.

797
00:56:23,816 --> 00:56:26,110
And I'm green and barfing.

798
00:56:26,360 --> 00:56:27,736
I knew that.

799
00:56:28,279 --> 00:56:30,572
You're wishing you were here
making me spaghetti...

800
00:56:30,823 --> 00:56:33,659
...so I wouldn't have to eat
Daddy's sucky lamb chop.

801
00:56:34,159 --> 00:56:35,619
You're right about that.

802
00:56:35,828 --> 00:56:38,580
-See? I'm pathatelic.
-Telepathic.

803
00:56:39,289 --> 00:56:40,833
That's what I said.

804
00:56:43,168 --> 00:56:46,797
-When am I going to see you?
-Tomorrow after school.

805
00:56:48,132 --> 00:56:50,342
I was wishing I'd see you tonight.

806
00:56:52,094 --> 00:56:56,390
We'll have to have one of our
dream dates and meet somewhere special.

807
00:56:56,682 --> 00:57:00,978
In our dreams. Where haven't we been
in a while? How about Disneyland?

808
00:57:01,603 --> 00:57:03,814
Last time, the lines
were too long.

809
00:57:06,608 --> 00:57:07,818
The beach.

810
00:57:10,404 --> 00:57:12,447
On a hot summer day.

811
00:57:12,739 --> 00:57:15,158
With gigantic waves.

812
00:57:15,575 --> 00:57:17,035
And boogie boards.

813
00:57:17,244 --> 00:57:18,495
And corn dogs.

814
00:57:19,204 --> 00:57:20,497
Awesome.

815
00:57:20,789 --> 00:57:24,835
Cool! All right, don't forget
to put on your sunblock, okay?

816
00:57:26,419 --> 00:57:28,922
It's a dream.
You don't need sunblock.

817
00:57:30,340 --> 00:57:32,050
That's right. I forgot.

818
00:57:34,219 --> 00:57:36,012
Mommy, you still there?

819
00:57:36,972 --> 00:57:38,515
Ben? Time for dinner.

820
00:57:38,723 --> 00:57:40,433
I got to go.
See you tonight, okay?

821
00:57:40,684 --> 00:57:41,851
All right.

822
00:57:42,352 --> 00:57:44,396
I'll see you in my dreams.

823
00:57:45,063 --> 00:57:46,231
I love you.

824
00:58:10,088 --> 00:58:12,674
She doesn't have
that killer instinct.

825
00:58:12,924 --> 00:58:14,133
Defense, fall back!

826
00:58:33,861 --> 00:58:35,154
You feeling all right?

827
00:58:35,446 --> 00:58:37,156
Yeah, I'm fine. I'm great.

828
00:58:37,740 --> 00:58:39,450
You look a little tired.

829
00:58:39,659 --> 00:58:44,205
I hate when people say that. It's a
polite way to say you look like shit.

830
00:58:44,580 --> 00:58:49,126
-I didn't mean it like that.
-I just have some things on my mind.

831
00:58:54,507 --> 00:58:56,550
You've been really busy lately.

832
00:58:58,678 --> 00:58:59,679
Are you...

833
00:59:00,554 --> 00:59:02,014
...seeing somebody?

834
00:59:05,643 --> 00:59:08,813
No. I wish that was
the reason I was tired.

835
00:59:12,399 --> 00:59:14,693
I've been spending time
with my old boss...

836
00:59:14,985 --> 00:59:18,239
...trying to decide whether I'll
go back to Random House.

837
00:59:18,489 --> 00:59:20,449
Really? That would be great.

838
00:59:20,658 --> 00:59:23,577
Oh, Ben. Easy, easy, easy.

839
00:59:26,872 --> 00:59:28,582
Ben, Ben, be careful.

840
00:59:28,791 --> 00:59:31,710
You're a dead man, Captain Blood!

841
00:59:43,680 --> 00:59:44,890
That was cool.

842
00:59:45,849 --> 00:59:47,810
Sweetie, can you move your leg?

843
00:59:48,185 --> 00:59:49,186
Does it hurt?

844
00:59:49,561 --> 00:59:50,479
Are you okay?

845
00:59:51,021 --> 00:59:54,191
Yeah. Can I still go
to Tucker's party tomorrow?

846
00:59:56,735 --> 00:59:59,488
Probably. But we must
have somebody look at it.

847
00:59:59,821 --> 01:00:02,032
We'll go to the emergency room.

848
01:00:14,127 --> 01:00:15,837
-Five stitches.
-Is he okay?

849
01:00:16,088 --> 01:00:17,798
-He's fine.
-He's not crying?

850
01:00:18,131 --> 01:00:21,468
-Can I see my son now?
-I need your insurance information.

851
01:00:21,760 --> 01:00:22,928
I'll do this.

852
01:00:23,136 --> 01:00:24,930
He's in 1 52.

853
01:00:31,144 --> 01:00:34,147
-I don't see any broken bones.
-You don't have any.

854
01:00:34,397 --> 01:00:37,651
I'm very proud of you.
You were awfully brave today.

855
01:00:37,859 --> 01:00:42,322
It didn't hurt that bad. Besides,
it'll be cool to show my friends.

856
01:00:43,240 --> 01:00:45,283
Would you do me a favor?

857
01:00:46,409 --> 01:00:48,203
Maybe. Depends what it is.

858
01:00:48,703 --> 01:00:51,873
Will you ask Dad to give me
a white dove for Christmas?

859
01:00:52,082 --> 01:00:53,083
We'll see.

860
01:00:53,333 --> 01:00:54,250
Come on!

861
01:00:54,459 --> 01:00:58,129
Every magician needs a white dove.
A real one. They do.

862
01:00:58,588 --> 01:01:00,215
That's a long way off.

863
01:01:00,465 --> 01:01:03,885
I think we should talk
to your mom and just see, okay?

864
01:01:04,719 --> 01:01:06,262
Does it hurt again?

865
01:01:07,138 --> 01:01:08,139
Lay back.

866
01:01:08,348 --> 01:01:09,891
Take a deep breath.

867
01:01:13,436 --> 01:01:15,063
Will you sing me a song?

868
01:01:15,647 --> 01:01:18,399
My mom always sings to me
when I get hurt.

869
01:01:25,281 --> 01:01:27,659
Hard to think of
a song on the spot.

870
01:01:33,539 --> 01:01:35,333
If I needed you

871
01:01:37,293 --> 01:01:39,170
Would you come to me

872
01:01:40,797 --> 01:01:42,757
Would you come to me

873
01:01:44,967 --> 01:01:46,344
And ease my pain?

874
01:01:47,762 --> 01:01:49,555
If you needed me

875
01:01:50,932 --> 01:01:52,892
I would come to you

876
01:01:55,478 --> 01:01:57,521
I would swim the sea

877
01:01:59,023 --> 01:02:01,150
For to ease your pain

878
01:02:04,695 --> 01:02:05,863
Feel better?

879
01:02:06,197 --> 01:02:07,365
A little bit?

880
01:02:12,203 --> 01:02:13,996
It puts a girl on the spot.

881
01:03:15,307 --> 01:03:17,267
Hi. It's Jackie.

882
01:03:17,517 --> 01:03:19,645
I just got a call
from Random House.

883
01:03:19,936 --> 01:03:22,606
They want me to meet
an editor this afternoon.

884
01:03:22,814 --> 01:03:27,027
But I won't get back in time
to pick up Ben at Tucker's party.

885
01:03:28,445 --> 01:03:30,072
Good. Great.

886
01:03:33,158 --> 01:03:35,202
Ben will be happy too.

887
01:03:36,077 --> 01:03:37,787
That you'll pick him up.

888
01:03:38,121 --> 01:03:39,372
It's 4:30.

889
01:03:41,041 --> 01:03:43,251
At 22 Williams Road.

890
01:03:46,046 --> 01:03:46,880
Great.

891
01:03:49,299 --> 01:03:50,216
Thanks.

892
01:04:36,971 --> 01:04:38,765
How hard can this be?

893
01:04:54,071 --> 01:04:55,865
It's going to be okay.

894
01:05:02,622 --> 01:05:04,999
-Directory assistance. What city?
-Manhattan.

895
01:05:05,249 --> 01:05:08,169
-What listing?
-The number for Random House.

896
01:05:12,631 --> 01:05:14,592
May I speak with
Jackie Harrison?

897
01:05:14,842 --> 01:05:16,552
Mrs. Harrison's not here.

898
01:05:16,802 --> 01:05:19,055
She has a meeting
with the editor.

899
01:05:19,305 --> 01:05:22,725
I'm picking up Benjamin from
a party and I lost the address.

900
01:05:22,933 --> 01:05:24,977
I need to speak to her a second.

901
01:05:25,227 --> 01:05:26,687
I'm the senior editor.

902
01:05:26,896 --> 01:05:30,232
I haven't seen Mrs. Harrison
since she left Random House...

903
01:05:30,483 --> 01:05:31,942
... eleven years ago.

904
01:05:35,446 --> 01:05:38,115
Okay. Thanks anyway.

905
01:05:38,365 --> 01:05:39,199
Balloons.

906
01:05:39,533 --> 01:05:40,534
I beg your pardon?

907
01:05:40,784 --> 01:05:43,454
Look for a house with balloons.
It never fails.

908
01:05:43,704 --> 01:05:45,331
The kids will be there.

909
01:05:46,540 --> 01:05:47,833
Thanks very much.

910
01:06:35,380 --> 01:06:36,298
Look at you.

911
01:06:37,174 --> 01:06:38,300
Come here.

912
01:06:38,967 --> 01:06:39,885
Can you see me?

913
01:06:41,219 --> 01:06:42,846
You had a good time?

914
01:06:45,849 --> 01:06:48,518
Let's clean your shirt.
How was Tucker's party?

915
01:06:48,727 --> 01:06:49,644
Good.

916
01:06:51,438 --> 01:06:53,899
-Did he like the present?
-Yeah.

917
01:06:55,400 --> 01:06:57,902
Did they have the snake guy
or the magician?

918
01:06:58,153 --> 01:06:59,529
Snake guy.

919
01:07:00,864 --> 01:07:01,781
It bit Tucker.

920
01:07:02,282 --> 01:07:04,326
It bit Tucker? Did it eat him?

921
01:07:38,401 --> 01:07:41,404
Did you have trouble
finding the place?

922
01:07:41,654 --> 01:07:42,488
No.

923
01:07:43,156 --> 01:07:44,782
Well, thanks.

924
01:07:51,330 --> 01:07:52,373
I know your secret.

925
01:07:55,918 --> 01:07:58,212
I saw the tickets and note
from your new boss.

926
01:07:58,421 --> 01:08:01,757
You're not working at Random House
in New York. I talked to them.

927
01:08:01,966 --> 01:08:04,719
You're taking the kids
and moving to Los Angeles.

928
01:08:04,969 --> 01:08:07,263
What the hell are you doing,
reading my mail?

929
01:08:07,513 --> 01:08:09,640
Snooping around like some...

930
01:08:09,849 --> 01:08:10,933
...little dishonest--

931
01:08:11,183 --> 01:08:12,435
Dishonest?!

932
01:08:12,685 --> 01:08:16,188
I wouldn't have to snoop around
if you were honest with Luke.

933
01:08:17,773 --> 01:08:20,276
I'd have thought this
answered your prayers.

934
01:08:20,526 --> 01:08:24,363
You lose the witch and her two
little brats in one swoop.

935
01:08:24,655 --> 01:08:26,866
Simplifies everything.
You get your life back.

936
01:08:27,116 --> 01:08:30,744
There's lots of publishing houses.
Surely you can get a job in New York.

937
01:08:30,995 --> 01:08:35,291
I'm supposed to rearrange my life
to accommodate your schedules?

938
01:08:35,499 --> 01:08:38,669
If you're concerned,
why don't you get a new career?

939
01:08:38,878 --> 01:08:41,005
Why don't you and Luke
move to Los Angeles?

940
01:08:41,213 --> 01:08:44,717
You can rearrange everyone's life
without consulting us.

941
01:08:44,925 --> 01:08:47,595
Bi-coastal parenting.
People do it all the time.

942
01:08:47,845 --> 01:08:49,972
Luke gets the kids one month
during the summer...

943
01:08:50,222 --> 01:08:52,182
...and every other holiday.
It's not ideal but it works.

944
01:08:52,433 --> 01:08:53,809
No, you can't do that.

945
01:08:54,059 --> 01:08:56,020
You can't take
the kids away from him.

946
01:08:56,270 --> 01:08:58,522
-We can't live like that!
-We?!

947
01:08:59,732 --> 01:09:02,192
Luke has a problem,
tell him to talk to me.

948
01:09:02,443 --> 01:09:04,945
This is not about you.
This is not your problem.

949
01:09:05,863 --> 01:09:07,030
It is my problem.

950
01:09:07,239 --> 01:09:08,407
Why's that?

951
01:09:09,616 --> 01:09:11,410
Because I'm marrying him.

952
01:09:11,702 --> 01:09:15,455
We're going to share our
life together. I love him.

953
01:09:16,748 --> 01:09:20,085
His kids are everything to him,
and he would be devastated...

954
01:09:20,335 --> 01:09:22,045
...not to be near them.

955
01:09:47,362 --> 01:09:49,573
You guessed the wrong secret.

956
01:09:54,578 --> 01:09:56,621
Charlie Drummond...

957
01:09:57,664 --> 01:10:01,167
...is a colleague of mine from
Random House in New York.

958
01:10:02,877 --> 01:10:06,214
She moved to the West Coast office.
I'll crash with her...

959
01:10:06,423 --> 01:10:08,633
...while I get protein injections...

960
01:10:08,883 --> 01:10:11,386
...that are recommended
by my oncologist.

961
01:10:11,970 --> 01:10:14,514
You can only get them
in Los Angeles.

962
01:10:14,889 --> 01:10:16,182
Oncologist?

963
01:10:18,101 --> 01:10:19,185
Life's a tradeoff.

964
01:10:19,394 --> 01:10:22,730
It's finally legal to smoke dope,
but you got to have cancer.

965
01:10:28,987 --> 01:10:30,363
Are you dying?

966
01:10:36,244 --> 01:10:37,704
Not today.

967
01:10:47,630 --> 01:10:48,464
We'll beat it.

968
01:10:49,298 --> 01:10:51,092
It's a walk in the park.

969
01:10:53,511 --> 01:10:55,138
Thanks for the ''we.''

970
01:10:59,600 --> 01:11:01,894
You're not alone
in this, you know.

971
01:11:03,312 --> 01:11:05,356
You don't have
to go through this alone.

972
01:11:06,065 --> 01:11:07,608
You know that.

973
01:11:08,818 --> 01:11:10,862
You understand what I'm saying?

974
01:11:21,289 --> 01:11:23,249
What will we tell the kids?

975
01:11:26,752 --> 01:11:28,963
We should tell them the truth.

976
01:11:31,757 --> 01:11:33,384
They can handle it.

977
01:11:39,765 --> 01:11:42,309
It should've been me instead of you.

978
01:11:46,522 --> 01:11:48,399
I'll go along with that.

979
01:12:04,665 --> 01:12:05,874
Look out.

980
01:12:06,625 --> 01:12:08,419
You didn't see.

981
01:12:09,461 --> 01:12:10,921
Gotcha!

982
01:12:13,549 --> 01:12:16,009
Did he beat you?
Here, 35 marshmallows.

983
01:12:16,343 --> 01:12:18,804
35.
Your sister put them in.

984
01:12:20,430 --> 01:12:23,100
What's going on?
Who's marrying who this time?

985
01:12:23,350 --> 01:12:24,810
Mommy's marrying lsabel.

986
01:12:25,018 --> 01:12:26,311
So cute.

987
01:12:29,982 --> 01:12:32,234
-Guys, Mommy's sick.
-You still have the flu?

988
01:12:33,277 --> 01:12:36,697
I have cancer.
Do you know what that is?

989
01:12:39,199 --> 01:12:41,159
It's what Aunt Mary died from.

990
01:12:42,786 --> 01:12:44,746
Aunt Mary had a different kind.

991
01:12:44,996 --> 01:12:47,207
There's different kinds.
Hers was very...

992
01:12:47,416 --> 01:12:48,875
...very bad.

993
01:12:52,170 --> 01:12:53,713
Is yours bad?

994
01:12:54,673 --> 01:12:57,425
I've been working with a doctor...

995
01:12:57,676 --> 01:13:00,762
...and she says we have
every reason to hope...

996
01:13:01,054 --> 01:13:03,014
...that I'm going to be fine.

997
01:13:06,810 --> 01:13:09,187
Check this out. Look at this.

998
01:13:09,437 --> 01:13:10,438
So cool.

999
01:13:10,814 --> 01:13:11,982
It's okay.

1000
01:13:12,774 --> 01:13:13,525
Look at this.

1001
01:13:13,775 --> 01:13:15,986
I don't have to go to
the hospital for medicine.

1002
01:13:16,820 --> 01:13:18,363
It looks like Game Boy.

1003
01:13:18,697 --> 01:13:20,156
It kind of is.

1004
01:13:20,407 --> 01:13:22,742
It'll make me strong,
so I can fight the disease.

1005
01:13:22,992 --> 01:13:23,910
Cool.

1006
01:13:25,703 --> 01:13:27,080
Can I catch cancer?

1007
01:13:27,413 --> 01:13:29,958
No, sweetie.
It's not contagious.

1008
01:13:30,208 --> 01:13:33,044
So you've known about this
for a long time.

1009
01:13:34,504 --> 01:13:35,421
Yeah.

1010
01:13:36,464 --> 01:13:37,924
And you never told me.

1011
01:13:38,258 --> 01:13:39,342
Sweetheart...

1012
01:13:39,884 --> 01:13:42,262
...your mom wanted to wait
until the right time.

1013
01:13:42,887 --> 01:13:44,264
Guys, I'm sorry.

1014
01:13:44,514 --> 01:13:45,765
Look, I just....

1015
01:13:47,183 --> 01:13:48,893
I know how scared
I get when you're sick.

1016
01:13:49,143 --> 01:13:52,313
I thought it would be best
to wait until it got smaller.

1017
01:13:52,855 --> 01:13:55,692
So you lied.
You lied when you never told me.

1018
01:13:55,942 --> 01:13:59,278
Maybe you're lying now.
I can never believe you again!

1019
01:13:59,529 --> 01:14:00,446
I made a mistake.

1020
01:14:00,696 --> 01:14:02,156
People make mistakes.

