01:34:05,224 --> 01:34:09,144
I'm working on a Christmas project
for Ben and Anna...

1278
01:34:09,394 --> 01:34:12,731
...and there aren't any recent photos
of me with the kids.

1279
01:34:13,523 --> 01:34:14,900
I was just wondering...

1280
01:34:16,151 --> 01:34:17,527
...if you'd take some.

1281
01:34:18,362 --> 01:34:20,238
Sure. Love to.

1282
01:34:21,990 --> 01:34:22,908
Thanks.

1283
01:34:29,164 --> 01:34:32,000
Hey, guys, wait up.
Wait up for me!

1284
01:34:38,131 --> 01:34:39,758
Stop there for a second.

1285
01:34:39,966 --> 01:34:40,967
Great!

1286
01:34:42,302 --> 01:34:43,136
Perfect.

1287
01:34:43,345 --> 01:34:45,722
Benjamin, that's a dazzling
display of horsemanship.

1288
01:34:46,056 --> 01:34:47,933
Come on, you lazy horse, get up!

1289
01:35:01,696 --> 01:35:03,823
''One day, five men came
in funny hats...

1290
01:35:04,074 --> 01:35:07,160
...to pick the biggest, fastest,
roughest bull to fight...

1291
01:35:07,368 --> 01:35:09,746
...in the bullfights in Madrid.''

1292
01:35:35,813 --> 01:35:37,106
Hi, Mom!

1293
01:35:47,492 --> 01:35:48,743
Are you okay?

1294
01:35:49,076 --> 01:35:50,453
There we go.

1295
01:35:51,537 --> 01:35:52,788
Almost.

1296
01:35:53,456 --> 01:35:57,335
Well, almost not falling.
That was the first time he fell.

1297
01:35:57,710 --> 01:35:59,086
Awesome fall.

1298
01:35:59,378 --> 01:36:01,505
Are you going to try it again?

1299
01:36:02,131 --> 01:36:03,299
One over here. Everybody.

1300
01:36:04,508 --> 01:36:05,676
Cheese!

1301
01:36:08,846 --> 01:36:10,097
Are you going back?

1302
01:36:10,348 --> 01:36:11,182
More?

1303
01:36:11,807 --> 01:36:12,975
All right!

1304
01:36:13,225 --> 01:36:15,352
Go for it. I'm watching.

1305
01:36:21,942 --> 01:36:24,487
Ben was born in 2 hours,
went to the breast...

1306
01:36:24,737 --> 01:36:27,323
...and camped there
for the next four days.

1307
01:36:27,656 --> 01:36:29,200
Always with this...

1308
01:36:29,533 --> 01:36:33,913
...mischievous look on his face.
Like he had a secret or something.

1309
01:36:34,914 --> 01:36:36,457
And his...

1310
01:36:36,749 --> 01:36:37,666
...blanket...

1311
01:36:38,042 --> 01:36:41,045
...always looked like a cape.
Even the nurses said so.

1312
01:36:42,421 --> 01:36:45,090
He loves hearing that story
over and over.

1313
01:36:45,299 --> 01:36:47,593
About how he was born a magician.

1314
01:36:49,345 --> 01:36:50,512
And her?

1315
01:36:51,013 --> 01:36:52,639
Twenty-eight hours.

1316
01:36:53,891 --> 01:36:56,894
The doctors wanted
to go in and get her.

1317
01:36:57,728 --> 01:37:01,648
But I knew she'd come in her own time.
That's just the way she is.

1318
01:37:02,733 --> 01:37:04,693
Can't let anybody rush her.

1319
01:37:06,445 --> 01:37:08,238
I'll keep that in mind.

1320
01:37:30,427 --> 01:37:31,970
It didn't work, did it?

1321
01:37:33,221 --> 01:37:34,222
I'm sorry.

1322
01:37:35,557 --> 01:37:37,684
You did everything you could.

1323
01:37:39,186 --> 01:37:40,812
There are still options.

1324
01:37:41,062 --> 01:37:45,108
There's a treatment in Paris, one in
Switzerland, both recommended--

1325
01:37:45,358 --> 01:37:46,818
Thanks, but...

1326
01:37:49,070 --> 01:37:50,530
...l think I want to spend...

1327
01:37:50,864 --> 01:37:52,490
...my time at home...

1328
01:37:52,866 --> 01:37:54,326
...with my family.

1329
01:38:01,833 --> 01:38:04,335
Christmas will be here
before you know it.

1330
01:38:45,501 --> 01:38:49,881
-I thought you might need one of these.
-I do. It looks great.

1331
01:39:01,058 --> 01:39:02,226
A little more.

1332
01:39:02,602 --> 01:39:03,686
A little more.

1333
01:39:03,936 --> 01:39:04,937
Okay.

1334
01:39:05,187 --> 01:39:07,231
I think that's fine. Stop.

1335
01:39:07,732 --> 01:39:09,108
Perfect.

1336
01:39:10,401 --> 01:39:12,194
Smells great too.

1337
01:39:14,488 --> 01:39:15,573
Thanks.

1338
01:39:29,462 --> 01:39:31,922
What are we supposed to do
without you?

1339
01:39:34,300 --> 01:39:35,759
You'll be fine.

1340
01:39:37,553 --> 01:39:39,430
You're a great father.

1341
01:39:44,727 --> 01:39:46,520
I just never really....

1342
01:39:46,770 --> 01:39:49,523
I didn't give you
the chance to realize it.

1343
01:39:56,655 --> 01:39:57,573
Thank you.

1344
01:40:02,995 --> 01:40:04,371
Merry Christmas.

1345
01:40:24,891 --> 01:40:27,978
As for your pitiful knowledge
of what a woman really wants...

1346
01:40:28,228 --> 01:40:30,480
...l'm not wasting my time
on some loser...

1347
01:40:30,731 --> 01:40:33,233
...who doesn't even know
what snowblowing is.

1348
01:40:33,775 --> 01:40:34,735
Good one.

1349
01:40:35,402 --> 01:40:36,862
And the guy I see...

1350
01:40:37,154 --> 01:40:39,614
...is in high school, and
it has to be said...

1351
01:40:39,865 --> 01:40:43,285
...that every time we talk about you,
he laughs his ass off.

1352
01:40:43,660 --> 01:40:44,870
Yeah, right.

1353
01:40:45,537 --> 01:40:48,707
You don't believe me?
He's standing right over there.

1354
01:41:01,219 --> 01:41:02,304
No way.

1355
01:41:03,263 --> 01:41:04,723
Well, believe it.

1356
01:41:13,857 --> 01:41:15,567
You rule, Anna!
You rule!

1357
01:41:15,775 --> 01:41:16,860
You blew it!

1358
01:41:17,068 --> 01:41:18,111
Loser!

1359
01:41:26,911 --> 01:41:30,081
-What are you doing here?
-Picking up my kids from school.

1360
01:41:31,624 --> 01:41:32,875
Who is that?

1361
01:41:34,085 --> 01:41:37,922
He looks like that guy in his
underwear for Calvin Klein.

1362
01:41:38,172 --> 01:41:40,383
Fully dressed for Ralph Lauren.

1363
01:41:47,473 --> 01:41:49,267
He's such a loser!

1364
01:41:50,601 --> 01:41:51,519
Moron!

1365
01:41:57,358 --> 01:41:59,152
It worked, it worked, it worked!

1366
01:42:02,155 --> 01:42:06,033
Did you see the look on Brad's face?
Thank you so much!

1367
01:42:12,582 --> 01:42:14,917
Okay. ''Limp-dick'' I know.

1368
01:42:15,293 --> 01:42:17,336
What exactly is ''snowblowing''?

1369
01:42:19,213 --> 01:42:20,840
It doesn't matter.
I didn't explain it.

1370
01:42:21,340 --> 01:42:25,386
But I'll have to explain it to the
20 or 30 parents who call...

1371
01:42:25,678 --> 01:42:27,221
...in the next half-hour.

1372
01:42:27,513 --> 01:42:28,514
Give them my number.

1373
01:42:28,723 --> 01:42:31,392
I think they'll want to
talk to Anna's mother.

1374
01:42:31,642 --> 01:42:35,229
What are you worried about?
Looking bad at the PTA?

1375
01:42:35,896 --> 01:42:37,439
You defend what you did?

1376
01:42:37,690 --> 01:42:40,776
-Right to the ground.
-You put filth in my child's mouth.

1377
01:42:41,026 --> 01:42:42,820
You had her lie about that model.

1378
01:42:43,028 --> 01:42:45,364
And it worked like a charm.

1379
01:42:45,614 --> 01:42:48,617
And you became a hero,
and I became I schmuck.

1380
01:42:50,077 --> 01:42:53,080
Basically, you taught my child...

1381
01:42:53,455 --> 01:42:54,999
...that I am a loser...

1382
01:42:55,291 --> 01:42:57,251
...who doesn't care about her pain.

1383
01:42:58,460 --> 01:43:01,630
-That's not what I tried to do.
-That's what you did.

1384
01:43:02,131 --> 01:43:05,801
Did you think I didn't have some dirty
words for that little putz?

1385
01:43:06,051 --> 01:43:07,928
That I couldn't figure out
some low blows?

1386
01:43:08,178 --> 01:43:09,304
You weren't passing them out.

1387
01:43:09,555 --> 01:43:13,142
I believe, in a crisis, you have an
opportunity to learn something.

1388
01:43:13,392 --> 01:43:14,643
That's deep.

1389
01:43:15,477 --> 01:43:17,020
It was a lie.

1390
01:43:17,396 --> 01:43:20,732
Winning without dignity or grace
is not winning.

1391
01:43:20,983 --> 01:43:24,861
She has to figure out who she is,
so she can stand up to peer pressure...

1392
01:43:25,112 --> 01:43:26,822
...and steer her own course.

1393
01:43:27,030 --> 01:43:29,408
She wasn't steering
her own course.

1394
01:43:29,658 --> 01:43:31,785
She was steering yours.

1395
01:43:31,994 --> 01:43:34,746
That's what parenting
is all about, little girl.

1396
01:43:34,955 --> 01:43:38,542
They are pleading for you to
tell them how to do the right thing.

1397
01:43:38,792 --> 01:43:40,502
Sure as hell, that's
what you've done.

1398
01:43:40,752 --> 01:43:43,755
The next time something happens,
and the stakes are high...

1399
01:43:44,005 --> 01:43:48,135
...she'll look back and remember
how easy it was and how good it felt.

1400
01:43:48,385 --> 01:43:52,013
And she'll stand up for herself.
Dear God, what have I done?

1401
01:43:52,264 --> 01:43:54,599
You have turned her into you.

1402
01:43:57,769 --> 01:43:59,563
That's what this is about.

1403
01:44:00,564 --> 01:44:01,940
That's all it's about.

1404
01:44:02,148 --> 01:44:04,359
How would you know
what this is about?

1405
01:44:04,651 --> 01:44:06,194
You haven't been here
from the beginning...

1406
01:44:06,444 --> 01:44:09,614
...worrying every day that
the decisions you're making...

1407
01:44:09,864 --> 01:44:12,283
...will shape the people
they're going to be.

1408
01:44:12,742 --> 01:44:16,246
And you are not what
I want my children to be.

1409
01:44:20,875 --> 01:44:22,669
I don't want that, either.

1410
01:44:24,838 --> 01:44:28,883
This isn't about me or you.
It's about them.

1411
01:44:29,425 --> 01:44:32,178
And believe it or not,
I am trying.

1412
01:44:34,430 --> 01:44:36,891
And I do have their very...

1413
01:44:37,517 --> 01:44:40,019
...best interests at heart.

1414
01:46:10,317 --> 01:46:13,153
-Would you like a drink?
-Patrón, please. Double.

1415
01:46:15,656 --> 01:46:16,740
What's up?

1416
01:46:25,207 --> 01:46:27,876
Last year, I lost Ben.

1417
01:46:29,002 --> 01:46:29,836
What?

1418
01:46:30,045 --> 01:46:31,838
In the supermarket.

1419
01:46:34,424 --> 01:46:35,968
You're lying.

1420
01:46:36,218 --> 01:46:37,594
It's true.

1421
01:46:38,220 --> 01:46:41,556
That's impossible. You could
never lose that kid for one second.

1422
01:46:46,103 --> 01:46:47,270
I did.

1423
01:46:49,022 --> 01:46:50,899
Ben never mentioned it.

1424
01:46:51,817 --> 01:46:54,111
He just remembers I found him.

1425
01:46:55,821 --> 01:46:57,531
Why didn't you tell me?

1426
01:47:01,201 --> 01:47:02,661
You know why.

1427
01:47:10,001 --> 01:47:12,295
I never wanted to be a mom.

1428
01:47:15,840 --> 01:47:18,301
Well, sharing it with you
is one thing.

1429
01:47:20,428 --> 01:47:23,264
Carrying it alone
the rest of my life...

1430
01:47:25,183 --> 01:47:28,186
...always being compared to you....

1431
01:47:30,021 --> 01:47:30,980
You're perfect.

1432
01:47:32,524 --> 01:47:34,317
They worship you.

1433
01:47:35,568 --> 01:47:39,322
I just don't want to be looking over
my shoulder for 20 years...

1434
01:47:39,822 --> 01:47:41,199
...knowing...

1435
01:47:43,034 --> 01:47:45,411
...that someone else
would've done it right.

1436
01:47:46,496 --> 01:47:47,747
Done it better.

1437
01:47:48,665 --> 01:47:50,541
The way that I can't.

1438
01:47:51,918 --> 01:47:53,961
What do I have that you don't?

1439
01:47:56,089 --> 01:47:58,383
You're Mother Earth incarnate.

1440
01:47:58,925 --> 01:47:59,842
You're...

1441
01:48:00,551 --> 01:48:02,261
...hip and fresh.

1442
01:48:02,512 --> 01:48:03,513
You ride with Anna.

1443
01:48:03,763 --> 01:48:05,139
You'll learn.

1444
01:48:10,770 --> 01:48:12,730
You know every story.

1445
01:48:13,689 --> 01:48:15,233
Every wound.

1446
01:48:16,526 --> 01:48:18,152
Every memory.

1447
01:48:21,239 --> 01:48:24,951
Their whole life's happiness
is wrapped up in you.

1448
01:48:25,910 --> 01:48:28,579
Every single moment.

1449
01:48:31,874 --> 01:48:33,250
Don't you get it?

1450
01:48:36,087 --> 01:48:39,006
Look down the road
to her wedding.

1451
01:48:42,802 --> 01:48:44,261
I'm in a room...

1452
01:48:44,887 --> 01:48:46,514
...alone with her.

1453
01:48:50,309 --> 01:48:51,852
Fitting her veil.

1454
01:48:53,729 --> 01:48:55,439
Fluffing her dress.

1455
01:48:57,358 --> 01:48:58,651
Telling her...

1456
01:48:59,610 --> 01:49:02,947
...no woman has ever
looked that beautiful.

1457
01:49:12,373 --> 01:49:14,416
And my fear is...

1458
01:49:16,377 --> 01:49:18,253
...that she'll be thinking:

1459
01:49:22,841 --> 01:49:25,177
'' I wish my mom was here.''

1460
01:49:28,805 --> 01:49:29,973
And mine is...

1461
01:49:31,391 --> 01:49:32,684
...she won't.

1462
01:49:39,358 --> 01:49:40,817
But the truth is...

1463
01:49:42,444 --> 01:49:44,655
...she doesn't have to choose.

1464
01:49:46,198 --> 01:49:47,991
She can have us both.

1465
01:49:49,910 --> 01:49:51,536
Love us both.

1466
01:49:53,538 --> 01:49:56,792
And she will be a better
person because of me...

1467
01:49:58,001 --> 01:49:59,711
...and because of you.

1468
01:50:03,298 --> 01:50:05,342
I have their past...

1469
01:50:08,261 --> 01:50:10,555
...and you can have their future.

1470
01:50:30,909 --> 01:50:32,786
Guys, it's Christmas!

1471
01:50:33,036 --> 01:50:33,870
Wake up!

1472
01:50:34,120 --> 01:50:36,581
I hope there's a white dove.

1473
01:50:39,876 --> 01:50:41,669
There has to be a white dove.

1474
01:50:41,920 --> 01:50:45,590
Hark, I hear the gentle
sounds of Benjamin.

1475
01:50:47,175 --> 01:50:50,595
We better get out there before
he opens all the presents.

1476
01:50:54,933 --> 01:50:56,643
Have a little patience.

1477
01:50:58,978 --> 01:51:01,105
Can I open my presents now?

1478
01:51:02,315 --> 01:51:06,235
Your mom wants you to go upstairs
and open presents with her first.

1479
01:51:06,486 --> 01:51:08,696
Then we'll open presents down
here, okay?

1480
01:51:10,531 --> 01:51:12,575
Okay. Me first.

1481
01:51:34,096 --> 01:51:35,973
Merry Christmas.

1482
01:51:36,891 --> 01:51:39,810
Sweetie, I think this
has your name on it.

1483
01:51:52,948 --> 01:51:55,326
A real magician's cape.

1484
01:51:55,534 --> 01:51:56,744
Awesome!

1485
01:51:58,204 --> 01:52:00,080
Come here, I'll help you with it.

1486
01:52:00,289 --> 01:52:02,499
What does it have all over it?
Could you see?

1487
01:52:02,750 --> 01:52:04,376
Pictures of me and you.

1488
01:52:04,668 --> 01:52:06,045
And this one right here?

1489
01:52:06,253 --> 01:52:07,087
See that one?

1490
01:52:07,296 --> 01:52:10,466
That's our first official photo
of you and me as a couple.

1491
01:52:10,841 --> 01:52:11,842
See that?

1492
01:52:12,051 --> 01:52:14,553
Did you know I was
good-looking right away?

1493
01:52:14,845 --> 01:52:18,349
Everybody in the hospital talked
about it. Are you kidding?

1494
01:52:18,599 --> 01:52:22,102
But this good-looking
was beyond my imagination.

1495
01:52:26,982 --> 01:52:28,525
Are you dying?

1496
01:52:34,656 --> 01:52:35,949
What do you think?

1497
01:52:36,575 --> 01:52:37,659
Yes.

1498
01:52:38,619 --> 01:52:40,495
Then I won't see you anymore.

1499
01:52:42,289 --> 01:52:44,625
Well, you won't
see my body, but....

1500
01:52:46,084 --> 01:52:49,254
You know how a caterpillar
becomes something else?

1501
01:52:52,174 --> 01:52:53,133
A butterfly.

1502
01:52:54,926 --> 01:52:57,304
You just have to think of me...

1503
01:52:58,263 --> 01:53:00,307
...as off flying somewhere.

1504
01:53:00,974 --> 01:53:03,351
And, of course, the magician...

1505
01:53:04,144 --> 01:53:05,604
...knows the secret...

1506
01:53:06,313 --> 01:53:09,232
...that just because
you don't see something...

1507
01:53:10,275 --> 01:53:12,777
...doesn't mean it's not there.

1508
01:53:15,447 --> 01:53:16,907
So even though it might...

1509
01:53:17,240 --> 01:53:18,700
...seem like I'm gone...

1510
01:53:19,951 --> 01:53:21,828
...the magician knows better.

1511
01:53:24,247 --> 01:53:25,790
So where will you be?

1512
01:53:30,962 --> 01:53:32,130
Right here.

1513
01:53:32,464 --> 01:53:35,467
Right here, inside the magician.

1514
01:53:37,135 --> 01:53:38,928
Can I talk to you
when you're there?

1515
01:53:39,471 --> 01:53:40,555
Always.

1516
01:53:41,890 --> 01:53:43,850
You won't hear my voice...

1517
01:53:44,058 --> 01:53:45,935
...but deep inside...

1518
01:53:46,478 --> 01:53:48,271
...you'll know what I'm saying.

1519
01:53:51,316 --> 01:53:52,775
It's not good enough.

1520
01:53:56,237 --> 01:53:59,324
Of course it isn't,
because it isn't everything.

1521
01:53:59,532 --> 01:54:01,909
And we want everything, don't we?

1522
01:54:05,538 --> 01:54:07,582
But we still have one thing.

1523
01:54:07,915 --> 01:54:10,752
One of our greatest things
we'll always have.

1524
01:54:10,960 --> 01:54:12,587
You know what that is?

1525
01:54:14,047 --> 01:54:15,840
Our dreams.

1526
01:54:16,549 --> 01:54:19,218
We can still meet in our dreams.

1527
01:54:20,303 --> 01:54:22,263
We can talk to each other there...

1528
01:54:22,763 --> 01:54:25,433
...and go for walks together
in the summer...

1529
01:54:25,641 --> 01:54:27,351
...and in the winter,
and in the rain...

1530
01:54:27,560 --> 01:54:29,187
...and in the sun...

1531
01:54:30,354 --> 01:54:33,941
...and I can come and pick you up
and we can go flying.

1532
01:54:38,237 --> 01:54:40,573
Nobody's loved you like I do.

1533
01:54:42,491 --> 01:54:44,035
Nobody ever will.

1534
01:54:57,089 --> 01:54:59,925
-I brought you some tea.
-Merry Christmas, baby.

1535
01:55:00,176 --> 01:55:01,635
Merry Christmas.

1536
01:55:02,636 --> 01:55:04,597
Look what Mom made me.

1537
01:55:06,849 --> 01:55:08,893
I'll go show Dad and lsabel.

1538
01:55:09,101 --> 01:55:10,811
-Here.
-Thank you, sweetheart.

1539
01:55:13,939 --> 01:55:16,442
Will you make sure Dad knows
how to double-knot...

1540
01:55:16,692 --> 01:55:18,652
...my sneakers for school
in the morning?

1541
01:55:19,820 --> 01:55:20,654
Yes.

1542
01:55:21,697 --> 01:55:22,906
Thanks.

1543
01:55:26,702 --> 01:55:28,078
That's yours.

1544
01:55:38,005 --> 01:55:39,464
It's a quilt.

1545
01:55:40,007 --> 01:55:43,010
-And it has our pictures on it.
-Put it here.

1546
01:55:47,764 --> 01:55:50,434
It's like a scrapbook
you can keep warm with.

1547
01:55:51,643 --> 01:55:54,479
It's so beautiful. I've never
seen anything like it.

1548
01:55:54,688 --> 01:55:57,190
See the horse?
And your medals that you got?

1549
01:55:57,566 --> 01:56:01,611
Remember this dress you wouldn't
take off in Pre-K for 3 weeks?

1550
01:56:01,862 --> 01:56:03,113
Remember that?

1551
01:56:03,655 --> 01:56:06,116
Your first step.
Look at your foot.

1552
01:56:06,992 --> 01:56:10,662
Look at that little
chubby-cheeked thing. Look at you.

1553
01:56:15,542 --> 01:56:16,835
Are you scared?

1554
01:56:18,545 --> 01:56:19,754
A little.

1555
01:56:21,047 --> 01:56:22,674
Mostly, I was scared...

1556
01:56:22,924 --> 01:56:24,467
...for you...

1557
01:56:24,926 --> 01:56:28,013
...but I'm not anymore
because I know you'll be okay.

1558
01:56:31,057 --> 01:56:34,561
I don't want to say goodbye.
I'm going to miss you so much.

1559
01:56:35,687 --> 01:56:36,980
It's okay.

1560
01:56:39,024 --> 01:56:41,067
My sweetie. It's okay.

1561
01:56:42,444 --> 01:56:44,821
It's okay to miss me. It's okay.

1562
01:56:46,614 --> 01:56:48,158
You can miss me...

1563
01:56:48,366 --> 01:56:50,577
...and you can take me with you.

1564
01:56:51,202 --> 01:56:52,036
You can.

1565
01:56:52,453 --> 01:56:54,497
And when you're in trouble...

1566
01:56:54,831 --> 01:56:56,374
...l'll be there.

1567
01:56:56,749 --> 01:56:59,502
When you fall in love,
I'll be there.

1568
01:57:00,044 --> 01:57:01,337
You can.

1569
01:57:01,796 --> 01:57:03,172
I mean, that's how...

1570
01:57:03,590 --> 01:57:05,383
...people go on forever.

1571
01:57:05,592 --> 01:57:08,136
Because somebody takes them along.

1572
01:57:09,679 --> 01:57:11,639
On your graduation...

1573
01:57:11,889 --> 01:57:13,057
...and your wedding...

1574
01:57:13,349 --> 01:57:15,560
...and when you have your babies.

1575
01:57:18,020 --> 01:57:20,148
Take me along, will you?

1576
01:57:21,399 --> 01:57:23,651
Always, always and always.

1577
01:57:28,906 --> 01:57:31,159
You have made my life...

1578
01:57:31,659 --> 01:57:33,452
...so wonderful.

1579
01:57:34,704 --> 01:57:36,998
Take that with you too, okay?

1580
01:57:54,015 --> 01:57:56,142
Wow, Mom! It's so cool!

1581
01:57:57,852 --> 01:57:59,979
See what you got there, Ben.

1582
01:58:08,529 --> 01:58:11,115
What's the matter?
You look disappointed.

1583
01:58:12,741 --> 01:58:14,785
No, everything is great, Mom.

1584
01:58:16,078 --> 01:58:17,538
I love my presents.

1585
01:58:17,746 --> 01:58:18,872
Hey, guys!

1586
01:58:19,707 --> 01:58:21,333
Looks like we forgot one.

1587
01:58:24,169 --> 01:58:26,213
It's got your name on it, buddy.

1588
01:58:26,714 --> 01:58:28,257
Abracadabra!

1589
01:58:29,550 --> 01:58:31,844
What a beautiful cage.

1590
01:58:34,346 --> 01:58:35,389
It's empty.

1591
01:58:37,266 --> 01:58:38,559
Let's try it again.

1592
01:58:41,019 --> 01:58:42,396
I think maybe this time...

1593
01:58:42,688 --> 01:58:45,149
...you should say the magic words.

1594
01:58:45,691 --> 01:58:48,068
Abracadabra! Allakazam!

1595
01:58:48,277 --> 01:58:49,903
Allakazoom. Boom!

1596
01:58:52,364 --> 01:58:53,740
It worked!

1597
01:59:28,316 --> 01:59:31,903
Why doesn't everybody get
on the sofa for a picture?

1598
01:59:32,529 --> 01:59:35,448
Baby, can you put that birdcage
on the floor?

1599
01:59:39,369 --> 01:59:41,079
And I'll set up here.

1600
01:59:48,461 --> 01:59:51,631
On the count of 3,
I want to see big Christmas smiles.

1601
01:59:51,923 --> 01:59:52,841
One...

1602
01:59:53,216 --> 01:59:54,300
...two...

1603
01:59:56,511 --> 01:59:57,554
...three.

1604
01:59:58,638 --> 01:59:59,722
Excellent.

1605
02:00:00,765 --> 02:00:04,269
Good one. Now let's get one
with the whole family.

1606
02:00:11,359 --> 02:00:13,152
Okay. Let me just...

1607
02:00:13,653 --> 02:00:15,279
...reset this.

1608
02:00:18,700 --> 02:00:20,076
Get ready.

